    <h1>SNOW GLOBE SANTA SAFE FROM VIRUS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201119/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-19"><time>2020-11-19</time></a>
        - <span>THE BIG PICTURE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>If you are won­der­ing how Santa Claus is do­ing his usual meet-and­greet this year amid the pan­demic, this zoo in Aal­borg, Den­mark, could shed some light.</p>
    <p>As part of its Christ­mas in the Zoo event that started last Fri­day, the Aal­borg Zoo in­vited Santa to greet vis­i­tors from the in­side of a plas­tic dome, which was dressed up to look like a snow globe.</p>
    <p>The creative so­lu­tion not only met so­cial dis­tanc­ing re­quire­ments, but also brought much joy to vis­i­tors in need of hol­i­day cheer.</p>
    <p>Apart from meet­ing Santa, vis­i­tors could also par­tic­i­pate in Christ­mas work­shops and en­joy a walk through the zoo’s gar­den, which was dec­o­rated with Christ­mas lights.</p>

